    Classes in com.android.generics with type parameters of type Behaviour
    Modifier and Type Class Description
    class  Bucket<T extends Behaviour>
    this class takes a Generic data type, whose class implements the Behaviour interface.
    class  Kettle<T extends Animal,​V extends Behaviour,​E extends Number>
    can have more than one generic type, here we have three generic types T will be a type that extends the Animal class V will be a type that implements the Behaviour interface E can be any type of Number (Number is a superclass of all wrapper number classes Integer,Double,Float,Byte,Short,Long
    Fields in com.android.generics declared as Behaviour
    Modifier and Type Field Description
    private T Bucket.myBehave
    variable of type T will only have access to the methods in the Behaviour interface, which are happy(),mad(),sad() so this can be a While or a lemur, or an anonymous class implementation of the Behaviour interface
    (package private) V Kettle.myV
    myV can be a class that implements the Behaviour interface, which are Whale and Lemur can be a also anonymous class implementation of the Behaviour interface
